hot take: {% extends %} is the most underrated feature in all of web development.

React devs build elaborate component hierarchies, layout wrappers, context providers, and slot patterns to achieve what Django has done since 2005 with three lines:

{% extends "base.html" %}
{% block content %}
...your page here...
{% endblock %}

No imports. No props drilling. No build step. The base template defines the skeleton. Child templates fill in the blocks. Done. Boring. Perfect.

